cated task of screening and getting more than 100 passengers off the ship without potentially exposing themselves or the public to the virus. NBC’s Daniele Hamamdjian reports for Sunday TODAY.</description><expires>2056-05-10T12:17:54.000+0000</expires><guid isPermaLink="false">tdy_sun_hamadjian_hantarivus_cruise_260510</guid><link>https://www.today.com/video/hazmat-crews-evacuate-passengers-of-hantavirus-plagued-cruise-263068229823</link><media:content url="https://prodamdnewsencoding.akamaized.net/NBC_News_Digital/tdy_sun_hamadjian_hantarivus_cruise_260510/2/abs/index.m3u8" medium="video"><media:credit></media:credit><media:title>Hantavirus-Plagued Cruise Arrives in Canary Islands</media:title><media:player url="https://www.today.com/video/hazmat-crews-evacuate-passengers-of-hantavirus-plagued-cruise-263068229823"></media:player><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/mpx/2704722219/2026_05/1778415464862_tdy_sun_hamadjian_hantarivus_cruise_260510_S3_1920x1080-509wej.jpg"></media:thumbnail><media:description type="plain">The ship at the heart of the deadly hantavirus outbreak has arrived in the Canary Islands. Crews in hazmat suits have begun the complicated task of screening and getting more than 100 passengers off the ship without potentially exposing themselves or the public to the virus. NBC’s Daniele Hamamdjian reports for Sunday TODAY.</media:description><media:subTitle type="text/srt" lang="en-US" url="https://prodamdnewsencoding.akamaized.net/NBC_News_Digital/nbcnews/captions/2026/05/1778415464862_tdy_sun_hamadjian_hantarivus_cruise_260510.srt"></media:subTitle><media:subTitle type="text/vtt" lang="en-US" url="https://prodamdnewsencoding.akamaized.net/NBC_News_Digital/nbcnews/captions/2026/05/1778415464862_tdy_sun_hamadjian_hantarivus_cruise_260510.vtt"></media:subTitle></media:content><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/mpx/2704722219/2026_05/1778415464862_tdy_sun_hamadjian_hantarivus_cruise_260510_S3_1920x1080-509wej.jpg"></media:thumbnail><pubDate>Sun, 10 May 2026 12:17:51 GMT</pubDate><title>Hantavirus-Plagued Cruise Arrives in Canary Islands</title><updateDate>Sun, 10 May 2026 13:57:47 GMT</updateDate></item><item><dc:creator>Dennis Romero</dc:creator><dc:creator>Marlene Lenthang</dc:creator><dc:contributor>Suzanne Gamboa</dc:contributor><dc:contributor>The Associated Press</dc:contributor><dc:contributor>Reuters</dc:contributor><dateTimeWritten>Sun, 10 May 2026 19:19:06 GMT</dateTimeWritten><description>The hantavirus outbreak on a cruise that departed from Argentina last month has cast an unwelcome spotlight on Tierra del Fuego, a region well known for its biodiversity and bird-watching, authorities and guides say</description><expires>2112-01-01T00:00:00.000+0000</expires><guid>https://www.nbcnews.com/world/south-america/birders-defend-argentinian-city-avian-paradise-hantavirus-cruise-rcna344389</guid><link>https://www.nbcnews.com/world/south-america/birders-defend-argentinian-city-avian-paradise-hantavirus-cruise-rcna344389</link><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260510-magellanic-woodpecker-vl-1240p-15956f.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1333" width="2000"><media:credit>Science Photo Library via Reuters</media:credit><media:text type="plain">A Magellanic woodpecker is seen standing on a tree</media:text><media:description type="plain">A Magellanic woodpecker on a tree in Tierra del Fuego, South America.</media:description></media:content><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260510-White-bellied-Seedsnipe-vl-1253p-72344d.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1333" width="2000"><media:credit>Marc Guyt</media:credit><media:text type="plain">A white-bellied seedsnipe seen outside standing on moss</media:text><media:description type="plain">A Magellanic woodpecker on a tree in Tierra del Fuego, South America.</media:description></media:content><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260510-andean-condor-vl-1258p-ab434a.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="2001" width="1500"><media:credit>Joel Reyero</media:credit><media:text type="plain">An Andean condor looks over the snow-covered peaks</media:text><media:description type="plain">A Magellanic woodpecker on a tree in Tierra del Fuego, South America.</media:description></media:content><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260510-juan-petrina-vl-1229p-144bb2.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1333" width="2000"><media:credit>Cristian Urrutia</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Juan Petrina sits at a table in front of windows and points to a laptop screen with a pen as his arms rest on a notebook</media:text><media:description type="plain">A Magellanic woodpecker on a tree in Tierra del Fuego, South America.</media:description></media:content><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260510-Basanth-Sadasivan-mv-hondius-vl-1220p-ce4b7d.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1280" width="960"><media:credit>Courtesy Basanth Sadasivan</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Basanth Sadasivan poses with two thumbs up on the deck of a cruise ship, mountains can be seen behind him</media:text><media:description type="plain">A Magellanic woodpecker on a tree in Tierra del Fuego, South America.</media:description></media:content><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260505-cruise-rs-d79a42.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1665" width="2500"><media:credit>AFP via Getty Images</media:credit><media:text type="plain">CAPE VERDE-HEALTH-TOURISM</media:text><media:description type="plain">A Magellanic woodpecker on a tree in Tierra del Fuego, South America.</media:description></media:content><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260510-magellanic-woodpecker-vl-1240p-15956f.jpg" height="1333" width="2000"></media:thumbnail><pubDate>Sun, 10 May 2026 19:19:06 GMT</pubDate><title>As hantavirus fears mount, birders defend Argentine cruise city as avian paradise</title><updateDate>Sun, 10 May 2026 19:19:06 GMT</updateDate></item><item><dc:creator>Kaitlin Sullivan</dc:creator><dc:contributor>Berkeley Lovelace Jr. </dc:contributor><dateTimeWritten>Sun, 10 May 2026 12:00:41 GMT</dateTimeWritten><description>The Food and Drug Administration removed the black box warning from hormone replacement therapies late last year, and recently, the most insured type, the estrogen patch, has been in short supply amid a boom in the therapy’s popularity.</description><expires>2112-01-01T00:00:00.000+0000</expires><guid>https://www.nbcnews.com/health/womens-health/fda-estrogen-patch-shortage-hormone-therapy-alternatives-rcna344233</guid><link>https://www.nbcnews.com/health/womens-health/fda-estrogen-patch-shortage-hormone-therapy-alternatives-rcna344233</link><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-02/260203-hrt-partch-gk-a92e6b.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1667" width="2500"><media:credit>Miodrag Ignjatovic</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Female Applying HRT Patch for Hormonal Balance</media:text><media:description type="plain">Woman in the comfort of her home applies a hormone replacement therapy patch to her waist.</media:description></media:content><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-02/260203-hrt-partch-gk-a92e6b.jpg" height="1667" width="2500"></media:thumbnail><pubDate>Sun, 10 May 2026 12:00:41 GMT</pubDate><title>FDA claims there’s no estrogen patch shortage as women struggle to get prescriptions filled</title><updateDate>Sun, 10 May 2026